# OpsAgent: AI-Powered Kubernetes SRE

**OpsAgent** is an intelligent monitoring and automated healing platform for Kubernetes clusters. It combines traditional cluster observability with Large Language Models (LLMs) to provide "Self-Healing" capabilities for modern infrastructure.

## 🏗️ Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    User([User])
    TUI[Terminal UI - Textual]
    Web[Web Dashboard - React]
    API[FastAPI Backend]
    K8s[(Kubernetes Cluster)]
    AI[Groq AI - Llama 3]

    User <--> TUI
    User <--> Web
    TUI <--> API
    Web <--> API
    API <--> K8s
    API <--> AI
```

## 🚀 Key Features

*   **Real-time Intelligence**: Automatically diagnosticates crashing pods using AI summaries instead of just error codes.
*   **Dual Interfaces**: Switch between a terminal-optimized experience (TUI) and a premium web dashboard.
*   **One-Click Healing**: The "Auto Heal" feature triggers AI-assisted recovery actions (like smart restarts or resource adjustments).
*   **Visual Health Index**: A "Cluster Health Score" that gives an at-a-glance view of your infrastructure's vitality.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Component | Technology |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Backend** | FastAPI, Pydantic, Kubernetes Python Client |
| **AI Layer** | Groq SDK (Llama 3.3 70B) |
| **Web Frontend** | React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS (V2.1 Premium) |
| **Terminal UI** | Textual, Rich, HTTPX |
| **Deployment** | Docker, Kubernetes Manifests |
